# Random Password Generator

This is an advanced random password generator with a graphical user interface (GUI) developed in Python using Tkinter.

## Installation

1. Clone the repository:
git clone https://github.com/your-username/random-password-generator.git

2. Navigate to the project directory:


3. Install dependencies:
pip install -r requirements.txt

## Usage

1. Run the main script:

2. The graphical user interface will open.

3. Enter the desired password length and click on the "Generate Password" button to generate a random password.

4. Click on the "Copy to Clipboard" button to copy the generated password to the clipboard.

5. Do check "https://pypi.org/project/pyperclip/"
## Customization Options

- **Password Length**: The default password length is 8 characters. You can customize it by modifying the `length` parameter in the `generate_password` method of the `PasswordGenerator` class in `password_generator.py`.
- **Character Sets**: The password generator currently includes uppercase letters, lowercase letters, digits, and punctuation symbols. You can customize the character sets by modifying the `characters` variable in the `generate_password` method of the `PasswordGenerator` class in `password_generator.py`.

